{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567196","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567196"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:56:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:56:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18944"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18944","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18944"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.42,0.11,0.21,0.12]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11678"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80435"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11678","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11678"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18944"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65722"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4043"},{"type":"tags","id":"4697"},{"type":"tags","id":"4969"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"4985"},{"type":"tags","id":"6344"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27478"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43711"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80435","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80435"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 73-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with continuous urinary leakage for the past week. She underwent pelvic surgery for an ovarian mass two weeks ago. She reports constant wetness and has been using multiple pads daily. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHer medical history includes polycystic ovary syndrome, depression, breast cancer in remission, hypercholesterolaemia and rheumatoid arthritis. Her medications include sertraline, methotrexate, and atorvastatin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Pelvic examination reveals pooling of clear fluid in the vaginal vault. A tampon test with methylene blue-stained bladder content turns blue after 15 minutes.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Transvaginal ultrasound","CT cystogram","Intravenous pyelogram","Cystoscopy","Magnetic resonance imaging of pelvis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with symptoms and signs suggestive of a vesicovaginal fistula, which is a known complication of pelvic surgery. The continuous urinary leakage starting within the typical timeframe of 7-21 days post-surgery, along with the positive tampon test, strongly supports this diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECT cystogram\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate initial investigation as it provides detailed anatomical information about the size, location, and course of the fistulous tract. It has high sensitivity and can also identify other potential complications of recent surgery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETransvaginal ultrasound\u003C/strong\u003E may show the fistulous tract but has limited sensitivity compared to CT cystogram and may be uncomfortable for the patient in the early post-operative period.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMagnetic resonance imaging\u003C/strong\u003E can provide excellent soft tissue detail but is more expensive, less readily available, and generally reserved for complex cases or when CT findings are equivocal.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECystoscopy\u003C/strong\u003E can be useful to directly visualise the fistula opening but is invasive and may not provide information about the complete tract. It is often performed later as part of surgical planning.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntravenous pyelogram\u003C/strong\u003E would not be helpful in diagnosing a vesicovaginal fistula as it primarily evaluates the upper urinary tract.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Vesicovaginal fistula should be suspected in women with continuous urinary leakage following pelvic surgery.","CT cystogram is the most sensitive imaging modality for detecting vesicovaginal fistulae.","Most vesicovaginal fistulae present within 7-21 days following pelvic surgery."],"references":["Malik MA, Sohail M, Malik MT, Khalid N, Akram A. Changing trends in the etiology and management of vesicovaginal fistula. International Journal of Urology. 2018 Jan;25(1):25-9. Available online at ; https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/iju.13419","El-Azab AS, Abolella HA, Farouk M. Update on vesicovaginal fistula: a systematic review. Arab journal of urology. 2019 Jan 2;17(1):61-8. Available online at ; https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/2090598X.2019.1590033"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65722"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18944"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65722","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65722"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-20T17:36:08+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-20T17:36:40+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11678"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80435"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"6","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/6"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc75","name":"Geriatrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":nul